    // 
      PITCH GUIDELINES
      =======================================================================================

    section#about-section.about(style='padding-top:75px')
      .grid-container

        // ABOUT header 
        .grid-100.mobile-grid-100.tablet-grid-100
          header.section-header
            h2.section-title Pitch Guidelines
            h2.section-subtitle What Makes a Good Pitch?
          
          // ABOUT description 
          .about-box.grid-80.prefix-10.tablet-grid-100.mobile-grid-100(style='color: #000000;')
            h3
            strong
              | A good pitch should clearly and professionally address the following questions:
            br
            ol
              li
                | What is the product or service and what problem does it solve?
              li
                | Who is going to buy this product or service?
              li
                | What does the product/service cost? 
              li 
                | Who are the people building this solution?
              li 
                | What makes this product/service different from its competitors?
            strong
              | Additionally, pitches will be judged on the following criteria:
            br
            ol
              li
                | How creative, innovative, and novel is the idea?
              li 
                | The quality of the presentation - poise, skill, and clarity of pitch delivery.
              li 
                | Feasibility - realistic potential of the business, venture, or idea/innovation.   
            strong
              | Video pitches should be between 1 and 2 minutes. The entire pitch must be done by only one person and without the use of proprs or visual aides.
            br

    // 
      CATEGORIES
      =======================================================================================

    section#about-section.about(style='background-color:#fff')
      .grid-container

        // ABOUT header 
        .grid-100.mobile-grid-100.tablet-grid-100
          header.section-header
            h2.section-title Categories
            h2.section-subtitle Pitches must be made in at least one of the following categories
          
          // ABOUT description 
          .about-box.grid-80.prefix-10.tablet-grid-100.mobile-grid-100(style='color: #000000;')
            h3
            strong
              | Technology
            ol
              ul
              | Applies to products, services, or applications which involve primarily software or hardware innovation.
            strong
              | Non-Technology
            ol
              ul
              | Applies to products and services which do not rely heavily on technological innovation. 
            strong
              | Social Entrepreneurship
            ol
              ul
              | Applies to products and services which provide solutions to a well-defined social cause.                 
  
            strong
              | You may indicate which category you're submitting for, otherwise we will choose which category your idea most closely falls under. 
            br              
    // 
      FAQ
      =======================================================================================

    section#about-section.about
      .grid-container

        // ABOUT header 
        .grid-100.mobile-grid-100.tablet-grid-100
          header.section-header
            h2.section-title FAQ
            h2.section-subtitle Frequently Asked Questions
          
          // ABOUT description 
          .about-box.grid-80.prefix-10.tablet-grid-100.mobile-grid-100(style='color: #000000;')
            h3
            strong
              | Can I pitch more than once?
            ol
              ul
              | Yes, each student may submit up to 3 different video pitches. 
            strong
              | Can I pitch more than once for the same category?
            ol
              ul
              | Yes, but you may not submit the same pitch into multiple categories. 
            strong
              | Does the pitch have to be for an idea which I'm currently working on? 
            ol
              ul
              | Not at all - We encourage you to be creative and pitch an idea that you wish you were working on!                
            strong
              | When will I know if I'm selected as a finalist? What happens then?
            ol
              ul
              | We will be announcing finalists shortly after submissions close on May 18. You will then be invited to present a ten-minute pitch of your idea at the Perfect Pitch Summit on May 23 before a panel of judges, who will be selecting 3 winners to receive $1,000 each!
            strong
              | How can I attend the Perfect Pitch Summit? 
            ol
              ul
              | The Perfect Pitch Summit will be open for anyone to attend for free, and we will be posting the event registration soon!               
            br   

            strong
              | Have any other questions? Feel free to 
              a(href='mailto:contact@perfectpitch.io') contact us
              | !
            br

